{
  "text": "where A(x, x ′ ) denotes the affinity value between x and x ′ . Note that this is equivalent to finding the minimum normalized-cut in graph theory if the affinity matrix A is regarded as the adjacency matrix of a graph. It was shown that the above normalized-cut criterion is equivalent to a weighted variant of the kernel k-means criterion [CITATION_1] . Thus a slightly modified kernel k-means algorithm could be used for obtaining a local optimal solution of the normalized-cut criterion. However, the problem of frequently trapped by a local optimum still remains.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "1018454"
